This documentation describes the Splunk Firehose Nozzle for Pivotal Platform.
Splunk Firehose Nozzle integrates with Pivotal Platform Loggregator and forwards streaming logs and
metrics from user apps and system components of Cloud Foundry to Splunk Enterprise.
Pivotal Platform operators can then gain operational visibility over their Pivotal Platform
infrastructure, including the health and performance of their apps and system components.

For more information about Loggregator, see 
[Loggregator Architecture](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/application-service/loggregator/architecture.html).

## <a id="overview"></a>Overview

The Splunk Firehose Nozzle for Pivotal Platform Tile streams logs and metrics from Pivotal Platform and forwards them
to user-specified Splunk Enterprise indexers configured to receive data via [HTTP Event Collector](http://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/latest/Data/UsetheHTTPEventCollector).
Pivotal Platform operators and Splunk users can immediately search and analyze Pivotal Platform Firehose data from their
Splunk Enterprise deployment to build reports, dashboards, and alerts on the health
and performance of their apps.

Splunk Firehose Nozzle for Pivotal Platform includes the following key features:

* Setup with out-of-the-box data parsing and enrichment for various Pivotal Platform event types.
* Reliable event delivery by leveraging Splunk's HTTP Event Collector endpoint.
* Secure forwarding from Pivotal Platform into external Splunk environments using user-provided SSL certificates.
* Scales out to meet increasing data volume and number of apps.


